ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Our Shree sai sanstha was established on 11th Feb 1998. We are conducting activities for upliftment of people. As we know women form the major part of society and they must be treated royally , but practically they are not given the said position. So as to improve the status of women an association of women was formed known as Mahila Mandal. The main criteria behind this association were to motivate , spread & devlop their hidden talent. For this purpose various courses such as tailoring , preparation of food items etc. were held. In this way many employment opportunities for women were created. On the other hand women were made aware about the various schemes granted by Govt, so that they can get maximum advantage from that. Other Activities : Nursery school for children in remote and hilly areas and upliftment of the children for that purpose this sanstha undertaken the work for education of the village and specially for the children of SC / ST community in the rural area. Deaddiction: The Sanstha works to create awareness among youth against addictions and its evil effects. We are also planning to organize camps to guide them to a safer future. AIDS Awareness : AIDS is suppossed to be the threat to the mankind. The victim of AIDS are the people from 18-45 age group.If youth goes stray, we should bring them back. As the sanstha knows this danger we try to make the youth aware of this threat. 1st Dec to 7th Dec is observed as AIDS awaraeness week . The people from the family of an AIDS patient are given idea about how to treat them. Activities like Health camps, conducting of TB awareness camp in four district like raigad , ratnagiri , thane, pune from State Govt. and free check up camps for all the people held on independence and republican day. Our organization shree sai sanstha has participated in many social development programmes successfully like Charitable Hospital, Self Help Groups , Health Programmes, formed the unity of women together , cultural , agricultural activities. Sanstha has also conducted a 5 days Training Programme for Women Workers. Sanstha is now planning to take various short term activities all over India. We will be grateful to join you.
